&nbsp;</span></p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>话题：</strong></p>\n<p>\n\tWriting: imagine a scenario or express your opinion<br />\n\tDescription<br />\n\tDescription refers to an account of an observation or an object. What is the description? Who is giving the description? What is the importance?<br />\n\tThis week's topic: They gave a description... (90-110 words)</p>\n<p>\n\tSuggestions:<br />\n\t1) description of the suspect<br />\n\t2) description of the experiment result<br />\n\t3) description of the symptoms<br />\n\t4) description of the design<br />\n\t5) Instead of writing a scenario, feel free to comment on the story below.</p>\n<p>\n\t<strong>范例1：</strong></p>\n<p>\n\tNot only were the names of the dishes were listed on the menu, there were also description of the various dishes, listing the main ingredients and cooking methods. The food was divided into the main sections of appetizers, soups and salads, main course, and desserts. It was easy to find what he liked. The difficult part was choosing one thing over another. Of course, there were house <a class=\"hjdict\" href=\"http://dict.hjenglish.com/w/specialty\" target=\"_blank\">specialty</a> wines on the wine menu. The staff member taking the order was able to make great recommendations regarding what the wine pairing could be.</p>\n<p>\n\t想要得到专业主持人的点评和意见吗？<a href=\"http://st.hujiang.com/topic/169968521416/\" target=\"_blank\">快来节目现场一试身手吧&gt;&gt;</a></p>\n<br /><center><a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p869692/#relate_articles\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_chat.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a> <a href=\"http://www.hjenglish.com/new/p869692\"><img src=\"http://en.hujiang.com/2009/images/rss_digg.jpg\" style=\"border: 0;\" /></a></center><h3 style=\"margin: 10px;\">本周最热文章</h3><ul style=\"margin: 5px 0;\"><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/p823144/\">有声双语美文：别用恶意去揣测世界的爱心</a></li><li style=\"margin: 2px 0 2px 20px;\"><a href=\"http://en.hujiang.com/new/